lead_paragraph: VERIZON IS TO BUY YAHOO’S CORE BUSINESS Yahoo’s struggle to survive alone will soon come to an end. It has agreed to sell its core internet operations and land holdings to Verizon Communications, according to people briefed on the matter. The company, which at its peak was worth $125 billion, is now being sold for $4.8 billion. Yahoo shareholders will be left with about $41 billion of investments in Alibaba, Yahoo Japan and a small portfolio of patents.

headline_main: Clinton’s Candidacy Defined by Conflicting Portraits
byline_original: By Albert R. Hunt | Bloomberg View

abstract: A video biography at the Republican National Convention claimed that Mr. Trump built the Trump Golf Links at Ferry Point in the Bronx. But New York City built the course.
snippet: A video biography at the Republican National Convention claimed that Mr. Trump built the Trump Golf Links at Ferry Point in the Bronx. But New York City built the course.
lead_paragraph: Just before Donald J. Trump took the stage at the Republican National Convention in Cleveland on Thursday night, the actor Jon Voight narrated a breezy video biography of the candidate highlighting his can-do abilities.

abstract: Verizon has long been considered a front-runner to buy Yahoo’s core internet businesses. An announcement could come as early as next week.
snippet: Verizon has long been considered a front-runner to buy Yahoo’s core internet businesses. An announcement could come as early as next week.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The end of Yahoo as an independent company may be near, and Verizon — long considered the leading contender to buy the aging web pioneer — is the most likely acquirer.

abstract: The show’s creators have turned the travails of an anthropomorphic horse into a hilarious meditation on a peculiarly modern kind of unhappiness.
snippet: The show’s creators have turned the travails of an anthropomorphic horse into a hilarious meditation on a peculiarly modern kind of unhappiness.
lead_paragraph: Last winter, Michael Eisner, the television executive and former chairman of the Walt Disney Company, found himself sitting next to Michael Bloomberg’s longtime girlfriend, Diana Taylor, at a dinner in Aspen, Colo. At the time, Bloomberg was contemplating a third-party bid for the presidency. Eisner, who has never been shy about sharing his views, relayed two stories to Taylor he thought would help Bloomberg as he grappled with no longer being in charge of America’s most important city.

abstract: Elizabeth McQueen leaned on elected officials to revitalize Queensbridge Park in Long Island City. Its esplanade reopened in summer 2014, but her work still wasn’t done.
snippet: Elizabeth McQueen leaned on elected officials to revitalize Queensbridge Park in Long Island City. Its esplanade reopened in summer 2014, but her work still wasn’t done.
lead_paragraph: Into her 80s, Elizabeth McQueen patrolled Queensbridge Park in Long Island City, Queens, wheeling her walker, a grandson or a great-grandchild at her side, eyes sweeping the walks and lawn. “If someone was barbecuing, she made sure they had garbage bags,” her grandson, Desmen Williams, said. “She had a bin of supplies. A rake if you needed to rake up. She made sure the fire barrels were out there, so you put coals in the barrel when you were done.”
